      "source": [
        "## Corrección de Normalización para la predicción de la volatilidad para el SP500\n",
        "\n",
        "Al noralizar todos los datos antes de separar el 80 % de entrenamiento y el 20 % de comparación, algunos patrones de comportamiento se cuelan permitiendo una predicción mas sencilla, ahora, si normalizamos despues de separar los datos, esa ventaja se pierde y ahora da así.\n",
        "\n",
        "La razón por la que la corrección en la normalización no afectó significativamente los resultados es que, en este caso, la fuga de datos probablemente no estaba introduciendo una ventaja significativa. Aquí hay varias explicaciones:\n",
        "\n",
        "1️⃣ Los datos de entrenamiento y prueba tienen distribuciones similares\n",
        "Como estás trabajando con ventanas del índice de Hurst, los datos en el conjunto de prueba provienen del mismo proceso subyacente que los datos de entrenamiento.\n",
        "Si los datos de entrenamiento y prueba siguen distribuciones similares, entonces el impacto de la fuga de datos por normalización es mínimo.\n",
        "En otras palabras, aunque antes se usaba información del conjunto completo para escalar, la diferencia en la transformación fue pequeña."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6s5S_jSPIQJH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import yfinance as yf\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, LSTM, Dropout\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error, r2_score\n",
        "\n",
        "# Descargar datos históricos del S&P 500 con manejo de errores\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    sp500 = yf.download('^GSPC', start=\"1994-02-01\", end=\"2024-02-01\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    if sp500.empty:\n",
        "        raise ValueError(\"No se pudieron descargar los datos del S&P 500.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    if 'Adj Close' in sp500.columns:\n",
        "        sp500 = sp500['Adj Close']\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        sp500 = sp500['Close']\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"Datos descargados correctamente.\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"Error al descargar datos: {e}\")\n",
        "    exit()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calcular los rendimientos logarítmicos\n",
        "returns = np.log(sp500 / sp500.shift(1)).dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Función para calcular la volatilidad histórica\n",
        "def compute_volatility(series):\n",
        "    return np.std(series) * np.sqrt(252)  # Anualizada\n",
        "\n",
        "# Crear ventanas de datos para la red neuronal\n",
        "window_size = 60  # 60 días de datos para predecir la volatilidad\n",
        "\n",
        "# División en conjunto de entrenamiento y prueba\n",
        "train_size = int(0.8 * len(returns))\n",
        "train_returns = returns[:train_size]\n",
        "test_returns = returns[train_size:]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalización evitando fuga de datos\n",
        "scaler_X = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(-1, 1))\n",
        "scaler_y = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0, 1))\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test = [], [], [], []\n",
        "\n",
        "# Procesar datos de entrenamiento\n",
        "train_values = train_returns.values\n",
        "scaler_X.fit(train_values.reshape(-1, 1))  # Ajuste solo con datos de entrenamiento\n",
        "scaler_y.fit(np.array([compute_volatility(train_values[i:i+window_size]) for i in range(len(train_values)-window_size)]).reshape(-1, 1))\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(len(train_values) - window_size):\n",
        "    window = train_values[i:i + window_size]\n",
        "    X_train.append(scaler_X.transform(window.reshape(-1, 1)))\n",
        "    y_train.append(scaler_y.transform(np.array(compute_volatility(window)).reshape(-1, 1))[0])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Procesar datos de prueba\n",
        "test_values = test_returns.values\n",
        "for i in range(len(test_values) - window_size):\n",
        "    window = test_values[i:i + window_size]\n",
        "    X_test.append(scaler_X.transform(window.reshape(-1, 1)))  # Normalizamos con el mismo scaler_X\n",
        "    y_test.append(scaler_y.transform(np.array(compute_volatility(window)).reshape(-1, 1))[0])  # Normalizamos con el mismo scaler_y\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, y_train = np.array(X_train), np.array(y_train)\n",
        "X_test, y_test = np.array(X_test), np.array(y_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Definir la red neuronal mejorada\n",
        "model = Sequential([\n",
        "    LSTM(128, activation='relu', return_sequences=True, input_shape=(window_size, 1)),\n",
        "    Dropout(0.2),\n",
        "    LSTM(64, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    Dense(32, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    Dense(1, activation='linear')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')\n",
        "model.summary()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Entrenar la red neuronal\n",
        "model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=100, batch_size=32, validation_data=(X_test, y_test), verbose=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Hacer predicciones\n",
        "y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Inversa de la escala para la comparación en unidades originales\n",
        "y_test_inv = scaler_y.inverse_transform(y_test.reshape(-1, 1))\n",
        "y_pred_inv = scaler_y.inverse_transform(y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Cálculo de métricas\n",
        "def mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_true, y_pred):\n",
        "    return np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100\n",
        "\n",
        "mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test_inv, y_pred_inv)\n",
        "mse = mean_squared_error(y_test_inv, y_pred_inv)\n",
        "rmse = np.sqrt(mse)\n",
        "r2 = r2_score(y_test_inv, y_pred_inv)\n",
        "mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_test_inv, y_pred_inv)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n===== Métricas de Evaluación =====\")\n",
        "print(f\"MAE: {mae:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"MSE: {mse:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"RMSE: {rmse:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R² Score: {r2:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"MAPE: {mape:.2f}%\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Graficar la volatilidad real vs predicha\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
        "plt.plot(y_test_inv, label=\"Volatilidad Real\", alpha=0.6)\n",
        "plt.plot(y_pred_inv, label=\"Volatilidad Predicha\", linestyle='dashed', color='red')\n",
        "plt.title(\"Predicción de Volatilidad con LSTM\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
